thyme leaves and cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl. <strong><br><\/strong> "]},{"title":"Parmesan béchamel","content":["Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place milk, flour and butter into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>7 min\/90°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add reserved grated Parmesan and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","To assemble, cover the base of prepared casserole dish or baking tray with 3 pasta sheets, overlapping each sheet slightly. Spread ½ of the ricotta mixture over the pasta, then place another layer of pasta sheets over the top. Spread ½ of the zucchini mixture over pasta, then top with ¼ of the béchamel. Place another layer of pasta over the top of the béchamel and repeat layering process until all ingredients have been used, finishing with a layer of pasta and topped with a layer of béchamel.","Bake for 30 minutes (180°C) or until cooked and lightly golden.","Season with pepper, garnish with mint leaves and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pasta","content":["1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","200 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","2 eggs"]},{"title":"Ricotta, mint and spinach layer","content":["1500 g full cream milk","40 g white vinegar","½ - 1 lemon, zest only, no white pith, finely grated","8 fresh mint leaves, plus extra for garnishing","20 g fresh spinach leaves","1 pinch sea salt"]},{"title":"Zucchini, garlic and pea layer","content":["1 garlic clove","500 g zucchini, (approx. 1½ zucchini), cut into pieces","40 g olive oil","100 g frozen green peas","½ tsp sea salt","½ tsp ground black pepper, plus extra for garnishing","60 g dry white wine","2 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only"]},{"title":"Parmesan béchamel","content":["80 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into cubes (3 cm)","500 g full cream milk","50 g plain flour","30 g butter, softened"]}],"id":"r77120","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-SiZjAuByEnI\/XZWY8W2AUZI\/AAAAAAAAeFg\/gm08LpZeTlYlJhEH53BODl1UgF5s6KugQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_QBJmFLTaEE_GaFPi.png","title":"Ricotta, mint and zucchini lasagne","publishedAt":"2014-07-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"37.8 g","fat":"47.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"81.45 g","calories":"3844 kJ \/ 915 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, silicone bread mat, nut milk bag or muslin cloth, large bowl, rolling pin or pasta machine, casserole dish or deep-sided baking tray (20 x 20 x 5 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve lasagne with a fresh green salad.","This light and summery recipe is a great money-saver because you make the pasta and ricotta from scratch.","Roll out small amounts of pasta dough at a time and cover remaining dough with a damp kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out.","For best results after rolling and cutting pasta, allow to dry 1-2 hours on a lightly floured kitchen towel.","To increase quantity, add 1 extra egg per additional 100 g flour. The maximum quantity at any one time is 500 g flour and 5 eggs. Increase kneading time to 3 minutes."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","2h","4 portions"]}